Before we address the physics and event rate estimates of EMRIs, it is crucial that we have a good understanding of the kind of orbits that we might expect in the environments natural to COs in dense systems around a MBH. An important factor in understanding how a star can become an EMRI is the shape and evolution of its orbit. In this section, I will address these two aspects. First, we will not take into account the role of relaxation. The stellar potential in which our test star m∙\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
