The situation for EMRI production in the standard picture is more complicated than that of tidal disruptions by the MBH (e.g., Rees 1988; Magorrian and Tremaine 1999; Syer and Ulmer 1999; Wang and Merritt 2004) or GW bursts from stars on very eccentric orbits (Rubbo et al. 2006; Hopman et al. 2007) because these processes require a single passage within a well-defined distance Renc\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
