I now explain schematically how the FP equation is implemented numerically to follow the evolution of star clusters. A more detailed description can be found in, e.g., Chernoff and Weinberg (1990). In the most common scheme, pioneered by Cohn (1980), two types of steps are employed alternately, a method known as “operator splitting”:
